29/09/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police have arrested a man suspected of crimes committed against Croatian prisoners of war and civilians in the Glina prison during the 1991-1995 war, media reported on Tuesday (September 28th). A judge in Sisak has remanded Djuro Simunovic, 57, to custody. During the war, he served as a prison warden. (Tanjug, B92, Srna, Nezavisne Novine - 28/09/10)
